
A:
	I can't believe you threw that ball over the fence. Now you're going to have to go into that dark, scary, spooky forest all by yourself!

B:
	Then why won't you do it for us?

A:
	The lady you are expecting is Frau von Yburg?

B:
	It was he.

A:
	Hurry up! You're making me worried. [hears scream] What was that? Hold on!

B:
	No, I don't. But spare me!

A:
	Give me more time, Nina !

B:
	[Crossing to the right with the flagon.]  You asked about
Knut Gesling.

A:
	It hurts so much, make it stop!

B:
	I often play off jokes on you, it is true. But I don't know
how you will like this one to-morrow morning.

A:
	[_Rising_.]  I am afraid I must go, Lady Hunstanton.
Tuesday is always one of Mrs. Daubeny’s bad nights.

B:
	perfectly understand, M. le président. [_He reads_].[B]

A:
	Be quiet. 

B:
	What could he have done, poor boy?

A:
	Son of God deliver us.

B:
	Sorry--you won't let us try to help the town.
